The '''catspaw assassin''' is a minor character in the [[Season 1|first season]]. He is played by guest star [[Lalor Roddy]] and only appears in &quot;[[The Kingsroad]].&quot; He is never named, but is referred to as such in casting announcements and the script, a reference to a catspaw being someone unwittingly used to further another person's agenda.

sections.Biography:
===[[Season 1]]===
[[File:Dagger.png|thumb|The dagger belonging to the catspaw assassin.]]
The catspaw assassin was paid to kill [[Bran Stark]] while he is in a coma in [[Winterfell]], following his fall. The assassin arranges for a fire to start in the castle, reasoning it will draw people away from Bran's room. This diversion succeeds in persuading [[Robb Stark]] to leave the room, but [[Catelyn Stark|Catelyn]] remains behind. When the assassin goes into Bran's room to kill him, he finds Catelyn there. They struggle and he injures Catelyn's hand, but is then attacked by Bran's [[Direwolves|direwolf]], [[Summer]], who tears his throat out.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Kingsroad]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;

The assassin carried an elaborate dagger with a [[dragonbone]] hilt and a [[Valyrian steel|Valyrian steel blade]].Â Catelyn resolves to carry the blade to her husband in [[King's Landing]] to investigate further.&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Kingsroad]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; [[Petyr Baelish|Petyr &quot;Littlefinger&quot; Baelish]] falsely claims that the dagger belongs to [[Tyrion Lannister]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[Lord Snow]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; This leads Catelyn to take Tyrion prisoner when she chances across him at the [[Inn at the Crossroads]].&lt;ref&gt;[[Cripples, Bastards and Broken Things]]&lt;/ref&gt; Her actions spark a conflict between [[House Stark]] and [[House Lannister]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[The Wolf and the Lion]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt; Tyrion acquits himself of the crime via [[First Trial of Tyrion Lannister|trial by combat]] at [[the Eyrie]].&lt;ref&gt;&quot;[[A Golden Crown]]&quot;&lt;/ref&gt;
